author: gstein
msg: Switch the tree conflict maps over to svn_token.
* subversion/libsvn_wc/tree_conflicts.c:
(enum_mapping_t): removed
(node_kind_map, operation_map, action_map, reason_map): switch to
svn_token_map_t. simplify the sentinel -- we only care about NULL
(read_enum_field): change param to svn_token_map_t and rewrite in terms
of svn_token__from_mem().
(skel_prepend_enum): change param to svn_token_map_t and rewrite in
terms of svn_token__to_word().
* subversion/tests/libsvn_wc/tree-conflict-data-test.c:
(test_funcs): remove the test for writing invalid tree conflicts, since
this *does* get detected, and results in MALFUNCTION being raised.

author: gstein
msg: Switch the kind/presence mapping functions over to the token-based system.
Further iterations will be coming soon, but I wanted a quick verification.
* subversion/libsvn_wc/wc_db.c:

(word_to_kind, kind_to_word, word_to_presence, presence_to_word):
rewrite in terms of the token mapping tables and functions.
